{"meta":{"updateDate":1691007959636,"pPcc":"SAT#H","questionId":"6ac23de7","skill_cd":"H.A.","score_band_range_cd":1,"skill_desc":"Linear equations in one variable","createDate":1691007959636,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Algebra","ibn":"08682-DC","external_id":null,"primary_class_cd":"H","uId":"4338811f-2b65-4ee3-a639-d49c46eb016f","difficulty":"E"},"source":"legacy","detail":{"item_id":"08682-DC","section":"Math","body":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference \" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p1\"><p class=\"standalone_statement style:1 \">&nbsp;</p></div>\n","prompt":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction 4 x over 5, equals 20\"></span><p class=\"stem_paragraph \">In the equation above, what is the value of <span class=\"italic\">x</span> ?</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n","answer":{"style":"Multiple Choice","choices":{"a":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">25</p>\n"},"b":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">24</p>\n"},"c":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">16</p>\n"},"d":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">15</p>\n"}},"correct_choice":"a","rationale":"<p>Choice A is correct. Multiplying both sides of the equation by 5 results in <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"4 x equals 100\"></span>. Dividing both sides of the resulting equation by 4 results in <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 25\"></span>.<p>Choice B is incorrect and may result from adding 20 and 4. Choice C is incorrect and may result from dividing 20 by 5 and then multiplying the result by 4. Choice D is incorrect and may result from subtracting 5 from 20.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n"}}}